{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6cfdf2b9-46c1-4ce3-a382-c3d0fb4d234d","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but with important caveats:\n\n**Problems with your targets:**\n\n| Target | Issue |\n|--------|-------|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported — MSTest v3 targets `net6.0`+ for modern .NET |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Not supported — .NET Core 3.1 is out of support |\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. Replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`)\n2. Drop `netcoreapp3.1` entirely (or move to `net6.0`+)\n3. Update packages to MSTest v3 (`MSTest` meta-package or individual 3.x packages)\n\n**Other breaking changes in MSTest v3 to be aware of:**\n- `TestContext` changes (some properties removed/renamed)\n- `DeploymentItem` behavior changes\n- Some assert APIs have updated signatures\n- Class/assembly cleanup defaults changed\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3 compatibility?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a1b00f58-521a-4b41-a630-cf480d285969","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"B819:310A41:E7433F:F52069:6A044DFE"},"id":"5149c0c1-9fef-483d-b33c-df7b10f1cba0","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:10:17.641Z","parentId":"fa5d9e50-7e9e-4e18-b8c2-3174e4f2c0c2"}
